'''Laser pistol''' was a generic term for several types of handheld [[Blaster/Legends|blasters]].

==Behind the scenes==
The script for [[Star Wars: Episode IV A New Hope|the original film]] uses the term "laser pistol" to refer to various weapons used by [[Leia Organa Solo/Legends|Princess Leia]], [[Ponda Baba/Legends|Ponda Baba]], [[Han Solo/Legends|Han Solo]], and [[Luke Skywalker/Legends|Luke Skywalker]].<ref name="The Art of Star Wars Episode IV: A New Hope">''[[The Art of Star Wars Episode IV: A New Hope]]''</ref> The term is used only in narration of the action, never in dialogue, so it does not appear at all in the finished film, which instead uses "blaster" as the colloquial, in-universe term.

Along with alternate spellings '''lazerpistol''' and '''lazer pistol''', the term was used in earlier drafts of Episode IV.

[[Kenner Products|Kenner]] produced a toy it called a "laser pistol" as part of its first [[Star Wars (Kenner toy line)|''Star Wars'' toy line]] in 1977. The toy was modelled after [[Han Solo/Legends|Han Solo's]] [[DL-44 heavy blaster pistol/Legends|pistol]] from ''A New Hope''.

